      "created_at": "2016-05-21 07:46:50 UTC",
      "updated_at": "2016-05-21 07:48:38 UTC",
      "body": "I personally dislike the unicode arrows for several reasons. Most importantly, unicode arrow are not present in most standard keyboard layouts (hence, a tool is needed to insert them). Also, editing in vim I often run `dt=` to delete up to a `=>` but when the arrow is unicode I can't do that.\r\n\r\nI haven't heard a compelling reason why unicode symbol are better than regular ascii characters. I'm open to change my mind, so I assigned the \"up for debate\" label.\r\n\r\nFor now, my vote goes to encourage people to rewrite their unicode symbols to regular arrows:\r\n```\r\nfind . -type f -name \"*.scala\" -exec sed -i '' \"s/⇒/=>/\" {} \\;\r\n```\r\n\r\nPS. @easel Please use the thumbs up reaction instead of commenting +1."
    },
