      "updated_at": "2016-05-21 07:56:11 UTC",
      "body": "> True, but the AST remains unchanged.\r\n\r\nBy that argument, I could also ask scalafmt to [insert `{}` around multi-line expressions](https://github.com/scala-js/scala-js/blob/master/CODINGSTYLE.md#braces) (and remove them for single-line expressions), to [make then and else branches agree on using `{}`](https://github.com/scala-js/scala-js/blob/master/CODINGSTYLE.md#ifelse) or [appropriately use `()` vs `{}` in for comprehensions](https://github.com/scala-js/scala-js/blob/master/CODINGSTYLE.md#for-comprehensions), couldn't I? Now, you told me those were out of scope.\r\n\r\nI'm not complaining. I'm trying to understand the logic ;)"
