      "updated_at": "2016-05-25 18:49:49 UTC",
      "body": "I've found the unicode arrows a little easier to read, and since I have a tool to insert them I don't give it a second thought. My impression has been that scalafmt is trying to be an heir apparent to the more-or-less unmaintained scalariform, so feature parity would be nice."
