      "created_at": "2016-05-23 09:32:30 UTC",
      "updated_at": "2016-05-23 09:45:19 UTC",
      "body": "So far, the only intersection of options in scalariform and scalafmt is case arrow alignment. Feature parity has not been an objective, since those happy with scalariform can continue to use scalariform.\r\n\r\nI'm still willing to consider adding this option, but I would like to get more feedback from users who want it. I know that akka uses unicode arrows and I would be interested to hear their reasoning for that.\r\n"
    },
